A 72-year-old woman died at her farm in the Thornhill area on Saturday evening, according to police spokeswoman Captain Gerda Swart. &#8220;Her husband was admitted with burn wounds at a hospital in Port Elizabeth. Police have opened an inquest docket,&#8221; she said. Swart said emergency services have been deployed in the area since the start of the fires. &#8220;The Humansdorp cluster commander, Brigadier John Lebok expressed his heartfelt condolences to the family and friends of the victim.&#8221; A number of buildings and vegetation were also destroyed by fires in the area. Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share